South Africa Equity Market: Anglo Platinum, Impala, Standard

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a   a n d   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-03-11T15:46:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/south-african-equity-market-anglo-platinum-sasol-are-active.html
  South Africa ’s FTSE/JSE  Africa  All
Share Index rose for the first day in six, gaining 274.92, or
0.89 percent, to 31,173.86 as of the 5 p.m. close in
Johannesburg. The index fell 3.6 percent this week.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
South African market today.    Africa Cellular Towers Ltd. (ATR)  , a manufacturer of
steel communications towers, climbed the most since the stock’s
listing 2006, surging 6 cents, or 55 percent, to 17 cents. The
company said it had secured a 99 million rand ($14 million) in
funding from the Industrial Development Corp., a state-owned
lender, staggered over the next six years to provide working
capital and money for capital expenditure.    Anglo Platinum Ltd. (AMS)  , the world’s largest producer
of the metal, rose the most since Feb. 11, jumping 17 rand, or
2.6 percent, to 667.01 rand. Platinum prices increased 0.9
percent. Impala Platinum Ltd. (IMP SJ), the second-largest
producer of the metal, advanced 4.12 rand, or 2.2 percent, to
196.12 rand.  Standard Bank Group Ltd. (SBK SJ) jumped for the first day
in four, adding 1.23 rand, or 1.3 percent, to 97.33 rand. The
bank will sell its stake in  Russia ’s Troika Dialog to OAO
Sberbank, the country’s largest lender, for $372 million.
Africa’s largest bank may return capital to shareholders and
“buy commercial banks in Africa” following the sale, it said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
